title: Eureka Springs Fat Tire Festival- DH, STXC and OT
Eureka Springs Fat Tire Festival- Cross Country
Big Ballin' Dirt Track Classic
description: Big Ballin\' Dirt Track Classic is a non competitive training series held on the CARVE modified short track at Burn\'s Park in North Little Rock, AR.  It will be a three Saturday Series.
course: Purpose built 1.1 mile loop. There are bridges, roots, and a small climb
registration: Riders will be staged according to their USAC ranking.
directions: From I-40, take the Burn\'s Park exit and follow signs to the BMX track.  Registration and staging will be at the BMX track.

title: CHAMPION CYCLING CYCLOCROSS
description: Fort Smith Cyclocross Race, sponsored by Champion Cycling, is the first race in the Arkansas Cyclocross Series. It will be held at Springhill Park on Oct 24, 2010.  Net proceeds from this event go toward trail maintenance fund for the Fort Smith area.
course: Course is approximately .7 of a mile with 4-6 hurdles and a sand pit.  Most of the course is in an open area that is spectator friendly
registration: Available on-line at sportsbaseonline.com, by mail, or on race day.  Race day registration opens at 10:00 a.m. Registration is $30 for first event and $20 for subsequent events. Mtb category is $25.  Make Checks Payable to: FS Cyclocross.  Mail Checks to: Champion Cycling, 8201 Rogers Ave, Fort Smith, AR  72903  Race day registration Cash or checks only.
notes:
USAC rules apply
No sleeveless jerseys
Helmets must be worn while on bike
Promoter reserves right to adjust start times/combine events
No bar ends on Mountain bikes
directions: Race is at SpringHill Park near Lock/Dam 13 on Highway 59, east of Fort Smith, just off Highway 22 in Barling.

title: Bear Creek Bonfire & Brimstone Cyclocross Race
